<pictures>None</pictures><Review>Joe and his staff run an honest, high-quality, and fairly-priced business. He'll give you options to work with based on how much you want to invest or how much you can afford, which was incredibly valuable to me during the financial hardship of the pandemic. He's honest about what they can and can't do, will never try to upsell or use manipulative sales techniques to skimp on work and maximize profits. He does the job right at a reasonable price, and will always work with you to provide whatever he can within your budget.

We had a major engine issue in a car that was (rarely used, so a slow oil leak went unnoticed until it was too late) and ended up having to get the whole engine block replaced, and he quoted me a $1000 less than any of his competitors, which I quoted with 10 different shops prior to getting the recommendation to go to him. He did the work as quickly as possible and even threw in a towing job for free because he knew it was a major expense and any money I could save was a huge help at the time. It was finished within just a few days, and has been working fantastic ever since. A few months later I had to go back to get some other minor work, and then again recently for some issues from a hit-and-run while I was parked on the street, and he helped both times, with the same excellent experience, reasonable rates, and high quality service I'd come to expect.

Great people running an excellent shop that gives "small town" service and quality in the middle of the city. I would recommend his shop to anyone doing any kind of standard repair work, and I won't go anywhere else.< /Review>< rating>

< Review>
For 3 years my 2009 Ford Escape has made a rattling noise in the engine. I‚Äôve been to 6 different auto shops and have been told it‚Äôs the belt and they could change it for $1500, it‚Äôs the radiator ($1,000), nothings wrong with it, etc. etc. Nothing against my car but I wasn‚Äôt going to put $1,200 into a 12 year old car..

I took it to Joe, without an appointment to have my oil changed and mentioned it in passing as I was leaving. I was called 40 minutes later telling me it was the timing belt and he could replace it for $315 and change all my fluids. It was also done by 9 am the next day.

I COULD NOT BE HAPPIER with the service we received. My husband and I have not heard my car this quiet in years, we joked that we took the wrong car home. So thankful to have found Joe‚Äôs auto shop. We will be loyal customers as long as we live in southern ca.< /Review>

<text>Ship: Royal Princess. Traditional style of cruising. Service was as expected but we did find the staff to be a bit unenthusiastic. Would have liked a few more smiles and nice words.

Food was great and better than other cruise ships. For casual dining we especially liked the pizza place next to the pools on deck 16. Fresh delicious pizza slices all day!

Our favorite was the movies under the stars. Modern movies on the big screen, complete with popcorn and drinks! <text>Absolutely fantastic!!!

We had a fantastic cruise with this cruise line on the Sea Princess. Our cabin was great with a super comfy mattress; the dining rooms and specialty restaurants, cafes and bars were amazing; the quality and range of food was just as amazing (oh those desserts, especially those sinfully delicious Chocolate Journeys) and the entertainment was first class.  The magnificent atrium and shopping boutiques and salons were fun on those sea days.  Lots of fun activities including workshops and karaoke nights, and the table tennis, pool, spa and fitness center were all excellent.  The shore excursions were great and so well organised and to top it all off, the hardworking staff were all super friendly, always polite and helpful. It was an all round super amazing experience! There were a few minor irritations:

* speed of the onboard internet was sometimes a bit slow;
* some of the movies (e.g. Edward Scissorhands) were a bit old and pitched at the wrong passenger demographic;
* the photo staff were sometimes a little too much in your face.

However, our experience with Princess Cruises was overwhelmingly positive, hence the 5-stars and highly recommend.</text><Gmap_id>0x80c28750a5fc75a3:0xec627bb6f2e0baad< /Gmap_id>< Rating>

We immediately contacted Princess and EZ Air. No one could help schedule a new flight on 17 December. Qatar Airways was also closed. On 18 December, we contacted Princess, EZ Air, and Qatar Airways several times trying to get a flight to make the cruise that departed on 19 December from Singapore. After determining it was impossible to arrive in Singapore on time, the next port was Kota Kinabalu, Malaysia. Initially, we were told by Princess/EZ Air we couldn‚Äôt fly into Malaysia because we didn‚Äôt have Visas.  After advising the representative that we didn‚Äôt need visas as US citizens to fly into Malaysia, she found a flight that arrived after 6:00pm on 21 December.  The ship was scheduled to depart Kota Kinabalu at 8:00pm on 21 December. I asked the representative if the ship would wait until we arrived, and I was advised it was our responsibility to make the ship before it departed and the ship would not wait for us. We asked for other flight options into Kota Kinabalu that arrived earlier and none were available. According to the ship, the airport is only 5 minutes away from the port. It wouldn‚Äôt have been an issue if the representative on the phone said the ship would wait for us. We were told by Princess/EZ Air we could fly into Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam.  After expressing that our Visas we applied for allowed entry into Nha Trang, Vietnam by cruise ship, we were told we couldn‚Äôt fly into Ho Chi Minh City. According to the ship, a Visa is issued upon arrival at the airport and we didn‚Äôt need a visa prior to arrival. We were told by Princess/EZ Air we could fly into Bangkok, Thailand. After hours of phone calls and being on hold all day, we wanted to cancel the cruise. We were told that Princess would not refund anything and to contact the travel insurance for any reimbursement.  We were also told that we would have to get to the ship to receive any reimbursement for the days we missed. Finally, Vanessa Cameron in Customer Assistance was able to help us. She also reiterated that the ship would reimburse us the missed days. We arrived at the ship on 27 December while docked in Laem Chabang, Thailand. Once we got on the ship, we were directed to our room where we discovered the room was not decorated as promised for the anniversary celebration on 20 December and the 3rd bed was not set-up in the cabin.  Our steward informed us that he did not know we were coming. It was apparent the ship was not expecting us after waiting for our ship cards and our room not being ready. We went to the customer service desk and spoke with customer relations manager, Nilesh Mohite. We discussed our issues prior to arrival and discussed the issue with our room not being ready, and according to Nilesh, he entered a complaint on our behalf. We asked Nilesh if we could disembark in Singapore on 30 December, and he said he would contact the stateside office. Nilesh told us to contact customer relations to get our extra airfare reimbursed and the remaining 10 missed days reimbursed.</Text>

<Pics>None</Pics>< text>
I recently ran over a nail in almost brand new large truck tires, luckily it was not through the sidewall. I decided to call Valley Tire & Tackle in Fort Jones to see if they had time and the ability to repair my tire. They said it would be super quick and that yes they could fix it for around $10+ dollars.

So I went in around 45 minutes later. They quickly took the truck back into the shop and went about removing the tire and getting to work. After about 15 minutes they were done. They brought my truck back out front and told me no charge - on the house this time. So I gave the worker who helped a few dollars as a tip.

Overall, my first experience with them was fantastic. Customer service was outstanding, price (if I paid) was more than reasonable, and its local which I love to support where possible. I recommend giving these guys a call first before heading up to Medford or Yreka - give them a chance to earn your business. I will be returning.< /text>

< name>
Queen C</name>
<time>1621869051280<//time>< Rating>
4<//Rating>
< Text>
Met some friends for an early dinner on a Sunday. We arrived at 4 and we placed on the wait list which was 2.5 hours‚òπÔ∏è. If you're going to eat here get here as early as possible or have one person get there to put their name on the list and then everyone shows up around the time they quoted. Our wait time ended up being 30 min less than quoted. They will only seat if your whole party is there. They do seat a lot of large groups. The place is clean and there's lots of people moving around, it's a pretty well oiled machine. Our server pulled up with a cart that had the menu and bibs, napkins, lemons, seasoning and ketchup. We started with some Cajun wings, which were surprisingly pretty good. No batter just seasoned and fried. I ordered chicken strips and fries basket. It was typical but the lemon pepper fries were good. I'm glad the strips weren't over cooked and my friends ordered shrimp and mussels then they added eggs. They said it was seasoned well and tasted very good.
Overall it was a nice establishment just need to remember the wait time. We will be back.</Text>

<userid>115325747556853289185<//userid><username>Yiting H< /username>< time>
1536115352555< /time>
< rating>
5< /rating>
< text>
Pretty good experience.

The fries here were amazing! Very crispy on the outside and mushy inside!

The seafood here was overall fresh. We ordered shrimps, king crab legs and Dungeness crab with mixed seasoning. The seasoning was very flavourful and enjoyable! The corns that we added into the bags were so good!!

We had experienced a problem where we ordered 2 fresh, live Dungeness crab and one had an obvious foul, ammonia smell compare to the other one. We asked one of the waitress and she just responded that they only had the live crab at the time so they are all fresh, even though they offered the option of ordering the frozen crab. We later mentioned the problem to another waiter Bhu, he was very helpful on report the problem to kitchen and gave us a discount on one crab.

Overall our family had an excellent time!<//text>

< text>
This is not for everyone! However if you love shrimp and other boiled and seasoned seafood this is the place. We love this place! You must peel your own shrimp etc. However, you do get to pick the level of spice. Always fast efficient servers that are quick to refill drinks and provide more napkins. My family feels like they are at a New Orleans family picnic. Don't dress up or wear something you can't easily wash. Jump in and enjoy the food and experience.<//text>

The fries here were amazing! Very crispy on the outside and mushy inside!

The seafood here was overall fresh. We ordered shrimps, king crab legs and Dungeness crab with mixed seasoning. The seasoning was very flavourful and enjoyable! The corns that we added into the bags were so good!!

< time>
1562862699953<//time>
<Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
OMG!!! This place is amazing. I wish I could've brought this place back to Houston, TX with me. So good! So worth the wait. The wait time was an hour to an hour and a half so we decided to take it to go. That was a wait too. The place was super clean and well maintained, even the restroom. The house was packed with locals, that's always a good sign. We had to drive 20 minutes just to get back to our Airbnb to enjoy our meal. I ordered a pound of crawfish, a pound of snowcrab, and a corn. They were all amazing. Seasoned all the way through, just like home! Unfortunately, even though you order snowcrab by the pound which is about 2 clusters, they don't do that. It's about 1 cluster. I was so hurt, because they were so amazing. The staff were great and very friendly and patient. I will definitely revisit again if I'm ever back in CA.</Text>

< Rating>
5<//Rating>
< Text>
Oh my goodness.  This place is very much worth the wait, and the hype.  It started a bit awkward bc there were things I wanted that weren't on the menu.  The waiter made up for the inconvenience by suggesting other dishes that were more appropriate, and filling.  In fairness to the restaurant, our party arrived   close to closing time. I had the shrimp,  half pound...mind you  these shrimp still had the heads.  Never experienced that before. Quite the experience.  Also had King crab.  It was delicious.  I highly recommend this place to anyone who enjoys seafood.  Oh the also had a precarious way of setting the tables.  Wax paper instead of table cloths.  You need a plastic bib as well. You do get messy. Check them out,  and get there early  for a better selection.</Text>

< Review>
Food was pretty good, service was fantastic.

Only issue is the price is through the roof for boil-in-bag seafood. We get our bill for two adults, we think it comes out to ~$90, but it turns out that was just for HALF the meal, and the total was actually ~$150.
We ordered a little heavy and took home leftovers, but in my opinion, $150 for food for ~3 adults in this atmosphere is about 20-30% too high.

It was gonna be two stars but our waiters were bros.<//Review>

< review>
Way too expensive, messy, and food was not good at all.. Take a look at the pictures I've attached. It was an $80 mess for only 1 teenage son and myself.

My teenage son and I had dinner there to celebrate my birthday. Price on the menu for crab only said MARKET VALUE....I figured the damage couldn't be too bad if we ordered just one pound (the minimum order amount). He wanted shrimp and clams. We got the minimum order of those also and 1 fries and 1 soda. A whopping $80 bill came at the end of all this untasty mess.... I couldn't believe it. The food was not very good at all. I had a stomach ache after. For all this money,  they just put a plastic baggy of your entres on your table with half of it swimming in a messy liquid sauce. You have to dig into this mess and peel your own shrimp and cut the heads off yourself. The crab, you have to handle the painfully thorny shells as you break the shell to scrape out scraps of leg meat. The furniture is old and outdated wooden picnic tables and hard bench seats with aged and dirty looking dark varnish finish from probably the 70s or 80s (it appeared but not sure of actual age). They give you a cheap plastic bib like age babies bib, and cover the picnic table in plastic so it makes it easy for them to clean your table afterwards.

For $80 for a teenage son and myself to have a terrible dinner, it was a complete dissapointment and I will NEVER go back..... YUKK !

NOTE TO OWNER....POST THE ACTUAL PRICE OF THE CRAB AND OTHER ENTRE''S ON THE MENU INSTEAD OF JUST SAYING "MARKET VALUE".....A nice trick !</review>

Now when it comes to the food, you are only able to order the seafood in 1 pound increments and the sides in 1/2 pound increments, although I did hear some tables around us getting things like 1 1/2 pounds of seafood. ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

<rating>5<//rating><Review>I was a little nervous after reading some of the recent reviews, but we really liked this location.  It wasn't terribly busy when we arrived at 5pm on a Tuesday night, so that may have helped.  We much preferred the spacious interior where you weren't packed in like sardines like you are in Garden Grove.  I'm guessing their tip share policy is the reason others were displeased with the service, but all four or five people who waited on us did a fine job.  We don't go frequently enough to be certain, but most of us felt the sauce may not have been quite as hot as before, but it was actually just right.  So between the larger space and slightly closer distance, this will be our go-to Boiling Crab location.< /Review>< Pics>

I like going to Boiling Crab during the weekdays when the wait isn‚Äôt so long. During the weekends there‚Äôs always a long line, and it could take up to 1 hour and 30 minutes of waiting. I like having shrimp in the whole Shabang sauce. It tastes really rich. And the clams are fresh, I have never had fishy clams here. But always remember to ask for the market price when ordering crab or lobster. I have a friend who had a traumatized experience ordering king crab legs without asking the price beforehand...< /Review>

<UserId.>101054211711735298146< /UserId.><Name>Dean James< /Name><time>1566350451215< /time><rating>5<//rating><Review>It's always a treat to visit the Boiling Crab (Santa Ana, Ca location). It was a plus to know that it was 5 minutes from my hotel. I performed at the 32nd Annual Long Beach Jazz Festival that weekend so knowing I was going to visit my favorite Sefood spot was a treat, not to mention that I was also celebrating my birthday. I live in Houston Texas and for some reason, the Boiling Crab shut their doors quite a few years back. It was a spot I frequently visited and can't find anything else that was comparable. The crawfish, when in season, is always a staple along with the other shellfish they serve. My personal favorite is either the Snowcrab or Kingcrab in the mild cajun sauce. I love that combination/mixture of vietnamese & cajun seasoning! It's truly addictive! You can also find what's called "The whole Shabang", which is a combination of all the seasonings thrown together, salty, buttery, sweet and very garlicky.

In essence, theres no place like it. The customer service, considering it's always a packed house, is excellent. They treat you like you are the only one in the room. I highly recommend this spot if your ever in the westcoast and crave shellfish. I look forward to my next visit!!< /Review><pics>None</pics>< resp>
None< /resp>

<Review>Always a fun time & great food - at any of their locations.  Expect to eat with your hands on butcher paper! (so don't wear anything you love that can't be easily washed - when you leave you will smell of yumminess) - yes they have cool lobster bibs for everyone!!  If you have enough people or have enough room in your tummy, get the gumbo, fried catfish basket, and lemon pepper chicken wings!! I prefer the whole dungeness crab over the blue crab.  Shrimp is a good choice loved by many.  If anyone in your party hasn't had crawfish before, then I'd start with a 1 lbs bag.  Get the corn & sausage - you won't be disappointed. I prefer the fries over the boiled potatoes.  If you have a group that requires different levels of spiciness, then order one bag at the highest spiciness level (for dipping), then order all common bags to be at the lowest spiciness level. Lemonade is good! Great prices on beer! no dessert available (luckily there are plenty of dessert places nearby)< /Review><pictures>None<//pictures><Resp>None</Resp><GmapID>0x80dcdf2d944788c7:0x8d93c5c4ab8098c2<//GmapID></record></dataset><record>

<userid>115022157943888186362</userid>< username>
Sean Collier< /username>
<Time>1527168496954<//Time><Rate>4< /Rate>< review>
1st time.  A bit confusing, much of the prices are marketplace, which I understand, but you have to ask more questions than you want to to find out what's what price.  So decided on the shrimp it was 14 bucks a pound, seemed cheap, she asked what side?  Red potatoes, small additional $3 additional. But you don't want just shrimp and spice because it goes in a bag.  I also ordered Catfish and üçü automatically comes with.  So guy delivers bag of shrimp and says catfish coming.  I'm like hold on this is plenty and I was hungry, they cancelled order, that would have been way too much food. Now the food is fresh, but you have to peel the shrimp out with your hands it was a lot of work, so everyone's table was a mess.  You get a bib and a paper layed over top yo just throw your shells.  I had to ask the mom and daughter next to me how do you peel this they showed me on her plate so flipping nice of them, saved me.  Fun, tiring, priced right I thought if you know what to order.  I got out for about $25, including a beer.   Imbnotba huge fan of shrimp, but was priced right, I wanted the crab but I was a bit intimidated didn't want to walk out dropping $60 on dinner, next time I'll just get crab and side Ill see how that works. She was just suggesting I need to get multiple things; not sure I need to.  Wouldn't suggest bringing kids here if they're a first timer unless the parents want to do double work.  Would have been perfect to have some yummy buttered bread or a side of rice Ill have to check on that next time  when I'm not such a newbie.I bet they don't serve great bread but I get why, they want people to buy more fish.  Until next time Mr. Crab, coming for you.<//review>

<text>1st time.  A bit confusing, much of the prices are marketplace, which I understand, but you have to ask more questions than you want to to find out what's what price.  So decided on the shrimp it was 14 bucks a pound, seemed cheap, she asked what side?  Red potatoes, small additional $3 additional. But you don't want just shrimp and spice because it goes in a bag.  I also ordered Catfish and üçü automatically comes with.  So guy delivers bag of shrimp and says catfish coming.  I'm like hold on this is plenty and I was hungry, they cancelled order, that would have been way too much food. Now the food is fresh, but you have to peel the shrimp out with your hands it was a lot of work, so everyone's table was a mess.  You get a bib and a paper layed over top yo just throw your shells.  I had to ask the mom and daughter next to me how do you peel this they showed me on her plate so flipping nice of them, saved me.  Fun, tiring, priced right I thought if you know what to order.  I got out for about $25, including a beer.   Imbnotba huge fan of shrimp, but was priced right, I wanted the crab but I was a bit intimidated didn't want to walk out dropping $60 on dinner, next time I'll just get crab and side Ill see how that works. She was just suggesting I need to get multiple things; not sure I need to.  Wouldn't suggest bringing kids here if they're a first timer unless the parents want to do double work.  Would have been perfect to have some yummy buttered bread or a side of rice Ill have to check on that next time  when I'm not such a newbie.I bet they don't serve great bread but I get why, they want people to buy more fish. <user_name>Alice H<//user_name>< Date>
1475535160432<//Date>
<Rate>4</Rate>< Review>
you have not lived until you've ordered boiling crab to go...  and eat it in all its glory at home, with wholeshabang all over your face and no one there to judge.

calling in to order can be a little tough (think trying to win drake tickets from a radio station), but i did give it a couple of tries and eventually it went through.

took about 20-25 minutes for the order to be ready, but definitely beats waiting for a table for 1.5-2 hours!

they provide all the condiments you can possibly need to enjoy your feast at home, including fresh limes, salt and pepper, and ketchup.  bibs and table liners are not included though...  not sure if you can ask :)

with the convenience of it all, it's great if you don't want to wait for a table, but do count on lukewarm wholeshabang and cajun fries by the time you get home :(< /Review>

<Resp>None<//Resp><userid>113897371292918169007</userid>< pictures>
None< /pictures>
< review>
Boiling Crab!!! I have been to this location a few times & still hasn't disappointed. My most recent visit was this past Friday night with a group of 4 friends. The line was terribly long but the hostess asked us if we didn't mind taking a table for 4 and add a chair at the end. Of course I said "yes"...either wait 30-40 minutes or get seated right away. It was a no brainer.

I ordered the typical pound of shrimp, medium with the whole sha'bang. No need to go into detail about what it is but just in case your not familiar it's all the seasoning into one bag. I also ordered "XXX Cajun Fries". Wow these fries are super hot!!! Make sure you order a cold beer because you will need it. I prefer the fries extra hot because the flavor is better than the mild.

The service is always good here, well at least for me. Multiple servers were around to ensure the customers were happy with there food & experience. I was so glad we got there when we did because there were a flood of people in the front of the restaurant waiting for tables. I overheard the hostess say average wait was anywhere from 45 minutes to 1 hour. Eesh...Come early!</review>

<time>1408260571886<//time><rating>5< /rating>< review>
SHA-BANG sauce yum!

I love, LOVE eating at boiling crab.  I enjoy eating their pounds of shrimp, dungeons crabs, corn in cob all in the SHA-BANG sauce along with the sweet potato fries and a dozen of oysters. YUMMY!  I always CRAVE for it and wish I can eat it all the time. The boiling crab in Santa Ana is hip, very spacious and they provide flat screen TV's in every wall, great for entertainment and sports bars.  They have a big parking lot, but sometimes can be ridiculous to find a spot because this place gets really pack. Good customer service and friendly staff.

Tip: Try to come during non-peak hours for less wait time.< /review>

<Review>you have not lived until you've ordered boiling crab to go...  and eat it in all its glory at home, with wholeshabang all over your face and no one there to judge.

calling in to order can be a little tough (think trying to win drake tickets from a radio station), but i did give it a couple of tries and eventually it went through.

took about 20-25 minutes for the order to be ready, but definitely beats waiting for a table for 1.5-2 hours!

they provide all the condiments you can possibly need to enjoy your feast at home, including fresh limes, salt and pepper, and ketchup.  bibs and table liners are not included though...  not sure if you can ask :)

with the convenience of it all, it's great if you don't want to wait for a table, but do count on lukewarm wholeshabang and cajun fries by the time you get home :(<//Review><Response>None<//Response><gmapID>0x80dcdf2d944788c7:0x8d93c5c4ab8098c2</gmapID></record>
